Equation of State library and data base (EOSlib)

Primary Author:        Ralph Menikoff
        

Version 2.1.0 ( Jan, 2014)
------------------------------------------------

Terms of use are stated in file SoftwareRelease

------------------------------------------------

Currently runs under
          RedHat linux
	  
EOS models currently implemented
	IdealGas
	StiffenedGas
	Hayes			(see Tex/Hayes.tex )
    GenHayes
	VonMisesElasticPlastic
	EqPorous 		(see Tex/Porous.tex)
    MieGruneisen
    JWL
    Elastic1D
	
EOS parameters have units
	low level routines provided to convert units

-----------------------------------------------------
                    INSTALLATION
-----------------------------------------------------

1. To install EOS library and applications
   make install_src
# Files deposited in subdirectories: include, lib, bin
# log file in subdirectory logs/$(os)

1A. test installation
    make TestLib
# If it all works then should end with
Running TestShock
	TestShock passes
Running TestIsentrope
	TestIsentrope passes
Running TestIsotherm
	TestIsotherm passes
Running TestImpedance1
	TestImpedance1 passes
Running TestImpedance2
	TestImpedance2 passes

In case of trouble see src/README

-----------------------------------------------------------

2. Cleanup, all but source
   make WipeOut

-----------------------------------------------------------
                  END INSTALLATION 
-----------------------------------------------------------   

Directories
-----------
bin    			scripts and executables (in subdirs for OS)
include			include files from all libraries
lib			libraries (in subdirs for OS) needed to link executables
logs			directory for log files
TestAnswers		Results to compare tests with
out			Results from running test problems
Tex			documentation for types of equations of state
src			source code for eos lib
draw			source code for dgraph
pl			perl scripts (install needed to set paths)
GUI			Graphical interface for DataBase
tmp			temporary directory used by MaterialData.gui
			to place .dg and .eps files
			these are removed when MaterialData.gui exits

Top level files
---------------
makefile		commands for make
EOS.data		Data base of EOS parameters (example)
Units.data		Data base for units (example)
README			this file
SetEnviron		for debugging, sets environment variables
SetEnviron.csh			version for csh

Executables
-----------
bin/Wave.sh		calculates wave curve (shock locus or isentrope locus)
bin/Isotherm.sh 	calculates isotherm
bin/ImpedanceMatch.sh	shock in material1 impacts material2
bin/Data.sh		prints parameters from database file
bin/Plastic.sh		Computes Hugoniot Elastic limit for Uniaxial Strain EOS 
Run			similar to above: Run Data [arguments]
			needed to set environment variable SharedLibDir
bin/ColorDgraph.pl	dgraph, drawing program by Klaus Lackner
MaterialData.gui	Graphical interface for EOS data base

Additional Information available on WEB
---------------------------------------
Theory (shock Hugoniot, isentrope, Riemann problem)
Lecture Notes: Applications of Non-reactive compressible flow (Ralph Menikoff)
	http://t14web.lanl.gov/Staff/rsm/preprints.html#CmpFlwLec
LASL Shock Hugoniot Data (Marsh Ed.)
	http://lib-www.lanl.gov/books/shd.pdf
